text_Original: I remember being a kid in the 80s and watching a tv show where they said in the future you would talk to people over the phone and see them...and the device looked like a landline with a smal tv set attached to it, but it looked sooo awesome and unthinkable... so in a way this fails to impress me as much, looks more like an evoluion of the stuff we already have. Difference is instead of attempting to film the other person and represent them as realistically as possible it's actually an avatar where some features could be modified...Idon't quite get the point of that.....If avatars can be anything why not make yourself look 20 years younger, as a woman, a man, a boy or a dogfor that matter? also the goggles may be good for immersion but other than that would be a nuisance to use for example at a work meeting or where you have both people present and away....
